From: stopless-java-gc <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH 0048/N] FileDispatcherImpl.c: statvfs(64) bsd treated as macosx

`FileDispatcherImpl_setDirect0()` switches on `MACOSX` to pick
`struct statvfs` + `fstatvfs()` vs `struct statvfs64` +
`fstatvfs64()`. The 64-suffixed variants are Linux LFS64 extensions
that don't exist on FreeBSD/CheriBSD (where `statvfs`/`fstatvfs`
are already 64-bit on LP64).

Treat bsd like macosx: change `#ifdef MACOSX` to
`#if defined(MACOSX) || defined(_ALLBSD_SOURCE)` at both call sites.

Refs: docs/05_zgc_cheri_collision_report.md (patch 0048)

--- a/src/java.base/unix/native/libnio/ch/FileDispatcherImpl.c
+++ b/src/java.base/unix/native/libnio/ch/FileDispatcherImpl.c
@@ -354,7 +354,7 @@ Java_sun_nio_ch_FileDispatcherImpl_setDirect0(JNIEnv *env, jclass clazz,
 {
     jint fd = fdval(env, fdo);
     jint result;
-#ifdef MACOSX
+#if defined(MACOSX) || defined(_ALLBSD_SOURCE)
     struct statvfs file_stat;
 #else
     struct statvfs64 file_stat;
@@ -386,7 +386,7 @@ Java_sun_nio_ch_FileDispatcherImpl_setDirect0(JNIEnv *env, jclass clazz,
         return result;
     }
 #endif
-#ifdef MACOSX
+#if defined(MACOSX) || defined(_ALLBSD_SOURCE)
     result = fstatvfs(fd, &file_stat);
 #else
     result = fstatvfs64(fd, &file_stat);
